  "instructions": [
    "Combine ricotta cheese, parmesan cheese, and xanthan gum in a bowl. ",
    "Add beef, eggs, and all-purpose flour to the bowl and mix until a dough forms.",
    "Knead the dough for 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.",
    "Divide the dough into 4 equal pieces and roll each piece into a long rope.",
    "Cut the rope into 1-inch pieces to form gnocchi.",
    "Press the tines of a fork into the gnocchi to create texture.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. ",
    "Add gnocchi to the skillet and cook until crispy and golden, about 3-4 minutes per side.",
    "Add beef and cook until browned, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add nuka-pickle juice, garlic powder, and italian seasoning to the skillet and stir to combine.",
    "Simmer the sauce for 2 minutes until heated through.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley and grana padano, if desired."
  ],
